Records. CRI* ČER ČNG DON KHM KHE* KHR* KYI LUG LWI MYK* ODE* POL RIV* TER VIN ZAK ZAP [Nowicky 1864: 36; Łomnicki 1866: 7 , 1886: 207 ; Cherkunov 1889: 43 ; Lukjanovitch 1928: 250 ; Penecke 1928: 358 ; Tveritina 1959: 183 ; Mazur & Kuśka 1994: 305 ;
Kubisz et al. 1998: 270
; Nazarenko et al . 2003: 53; Volovnik 1993: 586].

Biology.
Primary and secondary grasslands, tree plantations; abundant in ruderal habitats. Adults occur in IV– IX. Oligophagous on 
Asteraceae
(
Zwölfer & Preiss 1983
; 
Zwölfer & Harris 1984
; 
Volovnik 1994a
).
